Andropogoneae Species

Michelle C. Stitzer

2024-12-19

Elionurus tripsacoides

Photo by Herbario Virtual FMB, licensed under CC-BY-NC 2.0

Assembly is haploid, and the genome is tetraploid. It has a haploid genome size of 4400 Mb, and has 10 haploid chromosomes.

Species herbarium records

Herbarium records of Elionurus tripsacoides from AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022 are plotted with black points, The sampled individual this genome was generated from is shown in a colored point. The green background shows the biogeographic ranges of all Andropogoneae species in AuBuchon-Elder et al 2022.

Figure 2 from the main text, with Elionurus tripsacoides highlighted with colored points.

Dotplot of Elionurus tripsacoides vs. Paspalum vaginatum.

Like dotplots shown in Figure 3 of the main text, this shows syntenic blocks in Elionurus tripsacoides along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum on the x-axis. As Elionurus tripsacoides is a tetraploid with a haploid, assembly, we expect 2 paths for any x-axis position.

Fractionation of Elionurus tripsacoides

Like plots shown in Figure 4 of the main text, this shows proportion of retained genes in Elionurus tripsacoides along the y-axis, vs P. vaginatum chromosomes on the x-axis. As Elionurus tripsacoides is a tetraploid with a haploid, assembly, we expect 2 lines for each subgenome.
